qas.question: How many hours of sunshine does the South West England region get each year?
What region of England benefits from the extension of the Azores High pressure area?

context: <a1_0>South West England<a1_0/> has a favoured location when the Azores High pressure area extends north-eastwards towards the UK, particularly in summer. Coastal areas have average annual sunshine totals <a0_0>over 1,600<a0_0/> hours.
